<Page
  title="About"
  subtitle="Gustavo Adrián Salvini · Software Engineer"
  description="About Gustavo Adrián Salvini and this software engineering blog."
>
  <p>
    I'm a Software Developer, IT Consultant, and Founder of <a
      href="https://ecimtech.com"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener">EcimTech</a
    >. I build purpose-driven digital products with a focus on quality, scalability, and impact.
    This blog explores software engineering, agentic development, and applied AI in real-world
    workflows.
  </p>

  <h2>Current Focus</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Agentic Software Development</strong> — designing and orchestrating multi-agent coding workflows
      with harness frameworks, sub-agent architectures, and context budgeting
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>LLM Context Engineering</strong> — managing context windows, compaction strategies, handoffs,
      and the mathematical limits of attention mechanisms
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Software Architecture</strong> — scalable frontend and full-stack systems, component-based
      design, and state management at scale
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Modern Web Development</strong> — React, Astro, Next.js, TypeScript, and the ecosystem around
      them
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>AI-Enhanced Development & Research</h2>
  <p>
    I actively research and develop solutions that leverage AI and LLM technologies to enhance
    software development workflows, product ideation, and digital solutions.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      Integrating <strong>OpenAI</strong>, <strong>Anthropic</strong>, <strong>Google Gemini</strong
      >, and open-source LLMs through API-based architectures
    </li>
    <li>
      Exploring <strong>Generative AI</strong> applications for software architecture support, content
      generation, and automation
    </li>
    <li>
      Building <strong>AI-augmented web tools</strong> that empower users to create, learn, and make better
      decisions faster
    </li>
    <li>
      Researching <strong>RAG systems</strong> (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) and <strong
        >semantic search</strong
      > integrations
    </li>
    <li>
      Investigating <strong>local LLM deployment</strong> options for privacy-centric AI solutions
    </li>
    <li>
      Designing <strong>harness frameworks</strong> for agentic coding — convergent envelopes, barrier
      functions, drift detection, and fork-join orchestration
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Engineering Philosophy</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Building, learning, evolving</strong> — knowledge sharing as a multiplier for growth and
      collective innovation
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Systems thinking</strong> — treating software development as an engineered process, not
      a creative exercise
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Constraints over instructions</strong> — structural barrier functions beat verbal rules
      in agentic and human teams
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Context is finite</strong> — whether human or machine, effective work requires managing
      the scarce resource of attention
    </li>
  </ul>

